About Hart Springs
Hart Springs has one of the Largest Spring-Fed Swimming Areas in the State of Florida.
Hart Springs is located along the Suwannee River Wilderness Trail as well as the Gilchrist Blueway Trail.
On the northern border of Gilchrist County you will find the Santa Fe River our western border you will find the historic Suwannee River.
The Gilchrist Blueway Trail consists of 55 miles of pristine riverfronts.
Take a scenic stroll on our half-mile-long boardwalk, you can see when the springs flows up out of the earth, then you can see how the freshwater flows down the run where it then merges with the famous Suwannee River. Enjoy the scenic Suwannee River, cypress hammocks, and upland pine trails.
Hart Springs has unlimited choices of exploration by bicycle where you can connect to the Florida Greenway trail as well there are numerous routes on improved rural roads.
Hart Springs Park and Campground is a family-oriented recreation area, accessible by car and boat.
Come and experience Southern Hospitality at it’s best!
